    <entry>
      <title>love is romantic but profound</title>
      <link href="/2024/06/04/love-is-romantic-but-profound/"/>
      <url>/2024/06/04/love-is-romantic-but-profound/</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<link rel="stylesheet" class="aplayer-secondary-style-marker" href="/assets/css/APlayer.min.css"><script src="/assets/js/APlayer.min.js" class="aplayer-secondary-script-marker"></script><p>Love is not only romantic but more profound.</p><p>Gathering for happiness is not from love.</p><p>Separating for individuality is not from love.</p><p>Love is together, seeking happiness from tolerance and delayed satisfaction.</p><p>Love is apart, suffering nostalgia from reflection and upgraded personality.</p>]]></content>
      
      
      
        <tags>
            
            <tag> love </tag>
            
        </tags>
      
    </entry>
    
    
    
    <entry>
      <title>love is complementary and contradictory</title>
      <link href="/2024/06/04/love-is-complementary-and-contradictory/"/>
      <url>/2024/06/04/love-is-complementary-and-contradictory/</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<link rel="stylesheet" class="aplayer-secondary-style-marker" href="/assets/css/APlayer.min.css"><script src="/assets/js/APlayer.min.js" class="aplayer-secondary-script-marker"></script><p>Love is about you, but not merely you.</p><p>Love is about him, but not merely him.</p><p>Love is not business talk, not causal chat, but mental construction.</p><p>Neither of you can lay bricks and print the house.</p><p>Cooperation required, love is an artwork fragile but delicate.</p>]]></content>
      
      
      
